  "description": "Sufi scholar and Sunni philosopher (1165–1240)",
  "bio": "伊本·阿拉比（阿拉伯語：أبو عبد الله محمد بن علي بن محمد بن عربي الحاتمي الطائي，西班牙語：Abenarabi，1165年—1240年）是一個安達盧西亞的蘇菲派神秘主義者、詩人以及哲學家。 蘇菲派稱他為「最偉大的大師」，他也可以被認為是一個真正的聖人。\n伊本出生於穆爾西亞。他的父親阿里·本·穆罕默德曾在Mardanish的軍隊服役。當伊本Mardanīsh於公元1172去世，阿里·本·穆罕默德迅速地向蘇丹蒙哈德效忠。他的家人從穆爾西亞搬遷到塞維亞。\n伊本的主要作品有《智慧珍寶》、《麥加的開示》、《摩蘇爾的遞降》、《使命之冠》等。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "Sufi scholar and Sunni philosopher (1165–1240)",
  "bio_en": "Ibn 'Arabī (July 1165–November 1240) was a Sunni Muslim Arab scholar, Sufi mystic, poet, and Muslim philosopher from al-Andalus, who exercised notable influence within Sufi metaphysics and Islamic thought in general. There are 850 works attributed to Ibn 'Arabi, though only 700 of these are considered authentic, and only 400 are extant. His cosmological teachings became a dominant intellectual framework in many regions of the Muslim world.\nHis traditional title was Muḥyiddīn (Arabic: محيي الدين, lit. 'The Reviver of Religion').",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}